  "prompt": "What does \"I always considered your feelings for your best interest. I wonder if you ever considered how I even feel about things, because you don't #needmesomealonetime\" mean?",
  "response": "The statement appears to express feelings of being unappreciated or overlooked in a relationship, particularly in terms of emotional support and consideration. Here's a breakdown of what it might mean:\n\n1. **\"I always considered your feelings for your best interest.\"**  \n   The speaker is saying that they have consistently prioritized the other person's feelings and well-being, acting with their best interests in mind.\n\n2. **\"I wonder if you ever considered how I even feel about things.\"**  \n   The speaker feels that their own emotions and needs have not been acknowledged or taken into account by the other person. There\u2019s a sense of imbalance in the relationship.\n\n3. **\"Because you don\u2019t #needmesomealonetime.\"**  \n   The hashtag suggests that the speaker feels the other person doesn\u2019t value or seek out quality time with them. They might feel neglected or unnecessary in the relationship.\n\nOverall, the message conveys a sense of hurt and frustration, highlighting a perceived lack of reciprocity in emotional care and attention. The speaker feels they\u2019ve been giving more than they\u2019ve received and is questioning whether their feelings matter to the other person.",
